1
00:00:01,840 --> 00:00:04,320
RASSMUSSEN:
You must not watch this.

2
00:00:08,080 --> 00:00:10,440
(BREATHING SHAKILY) I'm warning you.

3
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:11,560
You can never un-see it.

4
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:15,840
But if you do watch...

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,280
Gagan Rassmussen. I'm Gagan Rassmussen.

6
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:22,800
And this is Le Verrier lab
in orbit around Neptune.

7
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:24,520
(EERIE MOANING)

8
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,680
I've put things together
into some kind of order,

9
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:31,400
so that you can understand.

10
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:33,080
So that you can have some idea.

11
00:00:33,160 --> 00:00:35,320
Uh, there are bits missing.

12
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,520
Sorry about that.

13
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:39,720
Um, I don't fully understand
what's been going on here.

14
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,000
But uh...

15
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:43,640
This is what happened.

16
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,760
Stop staring!

17
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:57,320
RASSMUSSEN: They came from Triton.

18
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,080
This is Chopra.

19
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:00,880
Bit of an attitude in my opinion.

20
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:02,440
NAGATA: Calm down, pet.

21
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:06,360
CHOPRA: Well, it's ridiculous!

22
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:08,360
That thing's meant to be
a lethal fighting machine

23
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:09,680
-(POD HISSING)
-and it just moons around

24
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:10,960
like a lovesick puppy.

25
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:12,480
I could hear your ranting
from inside the pod, Chopra,

26
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:13,560
for the God's sake!

27
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:14,640
Feel better?

28
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:16,320
RASSMUSSEN: Commander Nagata.

29
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,360
Young for the responsibility.

30
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:20,160
Quite a baptism of fire, I'm afraid.

31
00:01:20,520 --> 00:01:21,600
DEEP-ANDO: Marvellous, ma'am.

32
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:23,760
All hail, Morpheus, eh?

33
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:25,560
RASSMUSSEN: Deep-Ando, conscript.

34
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:26,840
Likes to think of himself as the joker

35
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:28,000
of this little group.

36
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:29,200
Well, he did.

37
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:31,200
CHOPRA: Morpheus! Morpheus! Morpheus!

38
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:33,520
Sleep's the one thing left to us.

39
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:35,640
The one thing they couldn't
get their filthy mitts on

40
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:37,640
and now they're even grabbing that.
Colonising it!

41
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,800
Spoken like a true Rip.

42
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:41,000
CHOPRA: Oh, don't call me that.

43
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:43,280
And don't call me that "ma"am".

44
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:44,360
Give it a rest, pet.

45
00:01:44,440 --> 00:01:45,440
Give what a rest?

46
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:46,960
This is a mission, Chopra.

47
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,400
We find out what's
happened on Le Verrier

48
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:49,600
and then we all go home.

49
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:51,320
Keep your politics to yourself, okay?

50
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:53,880
I know someone who'd love to get
Chopra back to Triton, eh?

51
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:55,160
(DEEP-ANDO LAUGHS)

52
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:58,880
RASSMUSSEN: This one's
obvious from the markings, isn't it?

53
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:00,320
We all know a Grunt when we see one.

54
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,360
-NAGATA: Come on, behave.
-Ooh.

55
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:05,680
(DISTANT THUDDING)

56
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:07,880
(BEEPING)

57
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,400
Nearly there, kiddies.

58
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,880
RASSMUSSEN: These are the rescue crew.

59
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:17,160
Don't get too attached.

60
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,840
Everything you're about to see

61
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:20,640
is from their individual viewpoints,

62
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:22,800
all taken from the station itself.

63
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,560
The only footage available.

64
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,680
They came to find me.

65
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:30,680
This is my station, my lab.

66
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:38,120
I've pieced together
the rescue as best I could.

67
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:41,800
If you're going to watch,
then pay close attention.

68
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:43,480
Your lives may depend on it.

69
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:53,240
NAGATA: Emergency lighting only.

70
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:55,560
Grav and orbit stable.
There must be power.

71
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,560
NAGATA: Nothing.

72
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,360
No sign of anyone.

73
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:12,040
There was no crew.

74
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:14,920
No crew left.

75
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,440
They did find others, though.

76
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,680
Strangers.

77
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,000
NAGATA: What the hell happened here?

78
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,160
474: Hide seek.

79
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:28,160
Maybe they play hide seek.

80
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,440
CHOPRA: Hide "and" seek.

81
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:32,920
Why do they miss out words?
It's infuriating.

82
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,720
474: Chopra, don't be anger.

83
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,840
"Don't be angry!"

84
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:38,960
Is it so hard to breed them
to speak properly?

85
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:40,520
DEEP-ANDO: Oh, lighten up.

86
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,120
-CHOPRA: What now?
-Talk.

87
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:45,680
-What?
-People talk.

88
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,040
CLARA: Do you ever get the feeling like
you're being watched?

89
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,320
DOCTOR: Paranoia.

90
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,760
CLARA: Why is it so dark?

91
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,200
DOCTOR: Night-time setting.

92
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:54,240
Faulty filament. Three day week.

93
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:56,360
CLARA: So, orbit around Neptune?

94
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,160
DOCTOR: Ah, this close into the planet

95
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:01,600
they must have some pretty powerful
anti-grav shielding on board.

96
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:04,080
CLARA: Looks like a Japanese restaurant.

97
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:06,720
(GASPS) Have you brought me
to a space-restaurant?

98
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:09,000
DOCTOR: People never do that, you know.

99
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,360
Do what?

100
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:13,040
They never put the word
"space" in front of something

101
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,120
just because everything's all sort of

102
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,640
hi-tech and futurey.

103
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:19,800
It's never space-restaurant
or space-champagne

104
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:22,240
or space, you know, hats.

105
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:24,640
It's just restaurant, champagne or hats,

106
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:26,040
even if this was a restaurant.

107
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,920
CLARA: What about space-suit?

108
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,000
DOCTOR: Pedant.

109
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,080
(GUN POWERING UP)

110
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,040
Hello.

111
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,640
NAGATA: Are you crew?

112
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:38,480
Uh...

113
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,920
NAGATA: Are you crew?

114
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:49,400
Engineering stress assessors?

115
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:52,200
Yes. Yes, we are.

116
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,400
We're here to, uh...

117
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,880
We're here to, uh...

118
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:59,120
-To assess stress.
-Assess... Stress...

119
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,800
NAGATA: So what happened?

120
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:05,040
From the beginning of time?
That's a very long story.

121
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,160
(SOFTLY) Doctor.

122
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,360
Well... (SIGHS)

123
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:09,680
Well, we just arrived, you know,

124
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,040
and there was nobody about.

125
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,280
Well, what are you doing here?

126
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:19,280
Twenty-four hours ago
this station fell silent.

127
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:21,880
No comm signal, nothin'. Dead.

128
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:23,600
We've come to find out why.

129
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,120
Theories?

130
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:27,160
NAGATA: Could be anything.

131
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:29,280
Meteorite strike. Space pirates.

132
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:32,040
Ah, see!
Not just pirates, space pirates.

133
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:34,000
So, what, you are a rescue mission?

134
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:35,280
Yes.

135
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,520
Of four?

136
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,840
Cuts, pet.

137
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:41,080
Right. You're to consider yourself...

138
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:43,520
Part of the furniture?

139
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,040
...under my command.

140
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:48,120
-Okay. Really?
-Yes, really.

141
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,480
-CHOPRA: Come on.
-Oh, okay.

142
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:54,440
CLARA: We still don't know where we are.

143
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:56,160
Indo-Japanese.

144
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,320
Thirty-eighth century.

145
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:05,880
-Tuesday.
-Thirty-eighth century?

146
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,400
Mmm.

147
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:08,560
After the Great Catastrophe,

148
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:10,840
there was a tectonic realignment.

149
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,840
India and Japan, they are...

150
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,080
Sort of merged.

151
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,160
We still don't know where the rest

152
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:18,120
of the crew are though.
I mean, a place this size.

153
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:20,480
Hey, what?

154
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,400
Great Catastrophe?
What Great Catastrophe?

155
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:24,720
(CHUCKLES) Well...

156
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:27,440
You've got all that
to look forward to, haven't you?

157
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:29,240
Mind you,

158
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:32,000
this place looks as if it's been
dead for a long while now.

159
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,800
DOCTOR: What is it?

160
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:47,280
CLARA: I still
can't shake the feeling...

161
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:49,680
474: Eyes. Watch.

162
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,720
Eyes in sky.

163
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,240
CHOPRA: What the hell
is that supposed to mean?

164
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:54,680
Chopra not worry.

165
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:56,480
474 protect Chopra.

166
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:00,440
Chopra pretty.

167
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:01,520
Oh, for the gods!

168
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,040
Just back off!

169
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,120
(GRUNTING)

170
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,480
DEEP-ANDO: Oh, come on, now!

171
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,960
-(BOTH GRUNTING)
-NAGATA: Let him go, pet.

172
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,240
474: 474, sorry!

173
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:09,320
Let him go now!

174
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,400
Not help it!

175
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,520
(CHOPRA WHIMPERING)

176
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,200
He could have killed me!

177
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:25,000
NAGATA: That's how
they're grown, you know that.

178
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:26,960
They react to any attack.

179
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:29,800
"Grown"?

180
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,080
NAGATA: They might not
give 'em much upstairs,

181
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:34,080
but our friend here
certainly knows how to fight.

182
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,640
You'd be glad of her
in a tight corner, I'll bet.

183
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,200
CLARA: What does she mean "grown"?

184
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,280
DOCTOR: She's a Grunt, Clara.

185
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,960
They're bred in hatcheries.

186
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:44,000
Cloned muscles.

187
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:46,640
Low intelligence. Brute force.

188
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:48,120
Instant army.

189
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,480
That's disgusting.

190
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:53,880
Well, that's how they roll
in the 38th century.

191
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:55,760
(DISTANT GROWLING)

192
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,800
DOCTOR: Hold my hand.

193
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,040
CLARA: I'm okay.

194
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:11,440
DOCTOR: I'm not.

195
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:12,720
(GUN POWERING UP)

196
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,520
(CREATURE ROARING)

197
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,760
-Run! Run! Run!
-(GUNFIRE)

198
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:16,840
Run, run!

199
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,080
DEEP-ANDO: Follow me!

200
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:21,640
DEEP-ANDO: Straight ahead!
NAGATA: No!

201
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:23,600
-This way! Deep-Ando!
-DEEP-ANDO: Straight ahead!

202
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,640
Push anything in front of it,

203
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:29,720
we've gotta keep them out!

204
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:32,120
NAGATA: Deep-Ando. We've lost him.

205
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,560
CLARA: What the hell are they?

206
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:34,920
DOCTOR: Not pirates.

207
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,120
NAGATA: We've got to get Deep-Ando.

208
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,200
Where's your friend?

209
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,560
CHOPRA: Deep-Ando. I don't know. He's...

210
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,000
NAGATA: He's still out there!

211
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,160
(ROARING)

212
00:08:42,560 --> 00:08:44,040
NAGATA: 474!

213
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:46,120
(GRUNTING)

214
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:01,400
NAGATA: What the hell are they?

215
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:04,320
Where did they go?

216
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:10,440
-(DEVICE BEEPS)
-Chief Nagata, this is Deep-Ando.

217
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:11,920
Where did you go?

218
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,800
-(BEEPING)
-(DEEP-ANDO PANTING)

219
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:20,440
Nagata, this is Deep-Ando.

220
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:21,840
May the gods look favourably upon you.

221
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:22,920
(BEEP)

222
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,680
Nagata, are you there?

223
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:27,920
(BEEP)

224
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,920
NAGATA: Deep-Ando, this is Nagata.

225
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,960
May the gods look favourably upon you.

226
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:39,080
-Deep-Ando, are you there?
-(RADIO CRACKLING)

227
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,200
What are you doing?

228
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,760
DOCTOR: Finding out
what they're made of.

229
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,320
NAGATA: Deep-Ando, are you there?

230
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,440
CHOPRA: Send the Grunt.

231
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:47,360
-NAGATA: No.
-Why not? That's what it's for.

232
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:49,880
Look, he's still out there.
You can't just abandon him.

233
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:52,280
I need proper intel
before I risk anyone else,

234
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,320
including 474.

235
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,760
Keep trying the comms!

236
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,840
CHOPRA: Deep-Ando,
may the gods look favourably upon you...

237
00:09:57,920 --> 00:10:00,080
-CLARA: Well?
-Organic. Definitely, organic.

238
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:02,440
Blood cells, skin cells, mucus...

239
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:05,960
CHOPRA: Deep-Ando, may the
gods look favourably upon you.

240
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:07,040
Deep-Ando?

241
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,480
What are these?

242
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:10,320
-Morpheus.
-Morpheus?

243
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:12,720
Named after the god of dreams.

244
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,960
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah!

245
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:16,880
Not just this!

246
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,920
So, what are they then, sleep pods?

247
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,160
-More than that.
-(RADIO CRACKLING)

248
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:22,800
-Deep-Ando?
-(CRACKLING CONTINUES)

249
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:24,040
Deep-Ando, can you hear me?

250
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,240
NAGATA: Keep trying.

251
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,840
I could take a look at that, you know.

252
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:28,960
Triangulate the signal,
help you find your friend.

253
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,240
NAGATA: First, tell me
what those things are.

254
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:32,840
(RADIO CRACKLING CONTINUES)

255
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,240
Deep-Ando?

256
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,720
Deep-Ando, this is Chopra.

257
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,040
I'm getting a signal.

258
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,440
Deep-Ando, can you hear me?

259
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,800
Deep-Ando?

260
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:43,080
Deep-Ando, this is Chopra.
Can you hear me?

261
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,400
CLARA: Doctor!

262
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,320
-(ALARM BLARING)
-Clara?

263
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:48,560
# Bom, bom, bom, bom, bom, borm, born

264
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:50,640
# Bom, bom, bom, bom, bom, borm, born

265
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:52,600
# Bom, bom, bom, bom, bom, borm, born

266
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:54,560
# Bom, bom, bom, bom, bom, borm, born

267
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:58,200
# Mr Sandman, bring me a dream... #

268
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:00,960
-Clara?
-NAGATA: It's fine, it's just Morpheus.

269
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:08,760
What do you think you were doing?

270
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:10,480
Huh?

271
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,080
It dragged me in.

272
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:16,160
The wires, they were like snakes.

273
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,480
-Like it was alive.
-Are you okay?

274
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:19,280
Yeah, it just kind of
flicked over my eyes.

275
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:21,160
CLARA: Did I sleep?
CHOPRA: Yeah, you did.

276
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:23,840
CLARA: Why did it just grab at me?
DOCTOR: Semi-sentient.

277
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,160
It thinks it knows what's good for you.

278
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:27,320
You obviously needed 40 winks.

279
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,880
Clever little sleep pod.

280
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:31,640
You said it was something
more than that though.

281
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,200
NAGATA: Come on, everyone knows.

282
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:35,160
Well, let's just say,
for the sake of argument, that we don't.

283
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,960
What is Morpheus?

284
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:38,880
474:; Last pod.

285
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:40,960
This pod.

286
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:43,520
Not empty.

287
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:46,480
(MR SANDMAN PLAYING)

288
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:48,240
Oh, no. No, no.

289
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,320
Enough of that.

290
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:50,720
(MUSIC STOPS)

291
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:51,960
(WHIRRING)

292
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:54,680
(WHIRRING STOPS)

293
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,600
-(POD WHIRRING)
-(GRUNTS)

294
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,800
It's almost like...

295
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:03,880
Someone's...

296
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,320
CLARA: Careful.

297
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,080
(GUN POWERING UP)

298
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:11,920
CLARA: Here. Let me try.

299
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,440
Hello?

300
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:26,400
It's okay. We're not going to hurt you.

301
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:27,640
Will you open up now?

302
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:30,160
Come on.
Let's start with names, shall we?

303
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:32,640
Um, I'm Clara.

304
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:33,920
This is the Doctor.

305
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:38,120
CLARA: It's okay.

306
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:46,360
RASSMUSSEN: AA, this is where I come in.

307
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:47,440
Hello.

308
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:50,440
I wanted to get out of there.

309
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:53,440
Immediately. Of course I did, but, um...

310
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:57,160
This man, the Doctor...

311
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:59,120
He wanted explanations first.

312
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:01,800
So...

313
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:08,160
May the gods look
favourably upon us all.

314
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:13,560
Friends, we live in a time
of unparalleled prosperity.

315
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:17,880
A golden age of peace,
harmony and industry.

316
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:21,520
But every shift must come to an end.

317
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,480
Every working day must stop.

318
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:28,200
Of course we can
take stimulants to make that deadline.

319
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:29,280
(YAWNS)

320
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:32,360
To keep us propped up
through that important meeting.

321
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:36,280
But always, always,
sleep claims us in the end.

322
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:38,040
Until now.

323
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,800
Sleep deprivation pods?

324
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,440
Not exactly.

325
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,840
PRESENTER: Welcome Morpheus!

326
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:46,320
(MR SANDMAN PLAYING)

327
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:48,280
The Morpheus machine concentrates

328
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:52,680
the whole nocturnal experience
into one five-minute burst.

329
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:54,760
Now you can go
a whole month without sleep!

330
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:57,680
-A month?
-All the chemical benefits of rest

331
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:02,320
but freeing up the nights
to continue working, working, working.

332
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:04,560
To get the edge on your competitor.

333
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:06,240
To turn that extra profit.

334
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:08,680
That's insane. That's horrible.

335
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:11,640
Finally!
Someone who sees it for what it is!

336
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:14,000
Leave the Rip Van Winkles behind

337
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:17,600
and become one of a new
generation of Wide-Awakes!

338
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:19,400
The future is here.

339
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:21,840
The future is now.

340
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:25,720
Let yourself slip into
the arms of Morpheus.

341
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:29,000
-But sleep is...
-Terms and conditions apply.

342
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:33,120
Sleep is vital.
Sleep is wonderful. Even I sleep.

343
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:34,200
When?

344
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:35,960
Well, when you're not looking.

345
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:42,600
Morpheus is mine. My invention.

346
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:45,680
It's changed Triton society forever.

347
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,880
DOCTOR: So how does it work?

348
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:50,880
The pod sends out
a coded electronic signal

349
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:52,840
that acts on certain parts of the brain.

350
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:55,160
Changes the fundamental chemistry.

351
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,440
CHOPRA: It's disgusting.

352
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:59,080
Making people into bloody drones.

353
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:01,040
-I've said it before...
-NAGATA: Aye, you have.

354
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:03,680
Colonising our sleep! Is nothing sacred?

355
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:06,760
We spend a third of our lives asleep.

356
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,440
And time is money.

357
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:10,720
He's right, man. It's amazing.

358
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,760
Everyone on Triton's using it.

359
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:13,920
DOCTOR: Are they now?

360
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:19,240
"Sleep that knits up
the ravelled sleeve of care.

361
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:23,320
"The death of each day's life,
sore labour's bath.

362
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:25,880
"Balm of hurt minds.

363
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:29,240
"Chief nourisher in life's great feast.”

364
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:32,720
Congratulations, Professor.

365
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:35,600
You've revolutionised the lab our market.

366
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:37,360
You have conquered nature.

367
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,960
RASSMUSSEN: Thank you.

368
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:41,040
You've also created an abomination.

369
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:44,520
RASSMUSSEN: The Doctor said that
we had to find the other soldier.

370
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:47,680
And to find answers.

371
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:50,200
So we left the lab.

372
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:52,080
He thought that there
was some connection

373
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:54,960
between my Morpheus process

374
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:56,800
and those creatures that attacked us.

375
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:01,240
Anyway, you'll see, he had a theory.

376
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:05,440
-Sleep dust?
-DOCTOR: Sleep dust.

377
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:06,520
NAGATA: You're kidding.

378
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,800
What, do I look like I'm kidding?

379
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:09,000
Is this a kidding face?

380
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:10,880
Ask the crew of this station
if they're kidding.

381
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:12,320
Or what's left of them.

382
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,680
NAGATA: But sleep dust?

383
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:15,800
Yes.
The stuff in the corner of your eye.

384
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,760
The stuff you wipe away
every morning when you wake up.

385
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,520
That's ridiculous.
This is getting us nowhere.

386
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:20,760
Okay, how, Doctor?

387
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:23,320
How can those things
be made of sleep dust?

388
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:24,600
Well, when we sleep,

389
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:26,200
the mucus crust builds up in our eyes.

390
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:28,680
Blood cells. Skin cells.
That's what dust largely is.

391
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:30,080
Human skin.

392
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:32,920
But your meddling has evolved it.
Hot-housed it.

393
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,600
What used to be sleep in your eye

394
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:36,880
has turned into a carnivorous life form!

395
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:40,320
You can't just throw
accusations like that around!

396
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,440
CLARA: So the longer you're in Morpheus,

397
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:42,880
the more the dust builds up?

398
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:43,960
That's slander!

399
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:45,920
Lying there in those pods,

400
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,440
people are a ready-made food source.

401
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:49,200
CLARA: Well, where are they then?

402
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:50,880
Where's the crew?

403
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,480
Digested.

404
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:57,520
NAGATA: Come on,
we need to find Deep-Ando.

405
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:03,680
DEEP-ANDO: Come on. Oh, come on!

406
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,520
Must be an exit here somewhere.

407
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:06,960
(DEEP-ANDO BREATHING HEAVILY)

408
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:08,720
(RADIO BEEPS)

409
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:10,280
Listen to me.

410
00:17:10,360 --> 00:17:11,840
These things, they're everywhere.

411
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:15,200
For the gods' sake come and get me.

412
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:17,120
(CREATURE GROWLING)

413
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:28,960
NAGATA: But what about us?

414
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:31,200
We've all used the pods back on Triton.

415
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:32,600
Not all of us.

416
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:34,800
NAGATA: This isn't
a good time to be smug, pet.

417
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:36,520
DOCTOR: Well, my guess
is that the ones you're using

418
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:39,360
are pretty primitive
compared to what's going on up here.

419
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:41,840
These are a sort of Mach 2, yeah?

420
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:45,320
Obviously, I have tried
to improve the process.

421
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,600
Speed things up.

422
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:48,840
You succeeded there.

423
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:51,640
But how does the dust
become those creatures?

424
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:53,040
You saw what happened.

425
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:54,120
The dust conglomerates.

426
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,960
It moulds itself into humanoid form.

427
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:59,000
It's adaptable. It's clever.

428
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:01,240
-(DISTANT GROWLING)
-(GUN POWERING UP)

429
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:05,320
And it's coming for us.

430
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:06,960
Look, you came to rescue the crew.

431
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:08,800
I'm crew. So rescue me!

432
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:14,520
CLARA: How come
you're the only one left?

433
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:15,840
Because I hid.

434
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:18,240
I hid in the only place I thought those
monsters wouldn't find me.

435
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:19,800
Look, we've got to get out of here!

436
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:20,960
No, we can't leave this place

437
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:23,480
until there's not a trace of the dust
or your machines left.

438
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:25,680
-Or that's it for your lot.
-NAGATA: Our lot?

439
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,200
What do you mean?

440
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:30,840
Oh, the human race.

441
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:00,320
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE: Hey.

442
00:19:00,920 --> 00:19:02,680
Haruka Deep-Ando, 6-8-9-7. Let me in.

443
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:03,920
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE: I'd love to.

444
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:06,200
Well do it then.

445
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,840
My ID must be on the Corporation index.

446
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:10,840
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
You have to do the song.

447
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:11,920
What?

448
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:14,680
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE: You have to
do the song, Deep-Ando 6-8-9-7.

449
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:17,720
I haven't got time for this.

450
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,160
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Do the song, please.

451
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:20,960
What the hell are you talking about?

452
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:25,840
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE: After the Maha
Shivaratri/Oshogatsu/Christmas party

453
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:27,800
some of the crew reprogrammed me.

454
00:19:27,880 --> 00:19:30,080
-They did, did they?
-Yes.

455
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:33,480
In order to enter rooms,
everyone must do the song.

456
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:34,960
It's very amusing.

457
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:38,600
But you know who I am!
You just called me by my name!

458
00:19:38,680 --> 00:19:39,680
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE: Nevertheless.

459
00:19:39,760 --> 00:19:41,000
(SIGHS)

460
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,200
What song?

461
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:44,280
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
You know the one.

462
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:46,280
I don't!

463
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:49,240
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
Now you're just being silly.

464
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:50,680
Of course you do.

465
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:53,640
Silly, Deep-Ando 6-8-9-7.

466
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:54,880
You must know the song.

467
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:57,080
-Everyone here knows it.
- (CREATURE GROWLING)

468
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:02,320
I'm not from this station.
I'm on a rescue mission.

469
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:05,880
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
# Bom, bom, bom, bom, bom, bom, bomn... #

470
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:07,240
Morpheus?

471
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:09,880
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
That's right. The Morpheus song.

472
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,360
Oh, this is insane!

473
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:13,200
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
The song, please.

474
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:14,840
Morpheus.

475
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:17,440
# Mr Sandman...

476
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,720
# Bring me your dreams

477
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:21,760
# Make him the cutest... #

478
00:20:21,840 --> 00:20:24,120
Haruka Deep-Ando 6-8-9-7. Let me in!

479
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:26,400
-FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE: More please.
-(DEEP-ANDO SIGHS)

480
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:29,480
# Give him two lips, like roses in... #

481
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:30,880
Please, let me in!

482
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:32,320
Let me in!

483
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:34,240
Let me in!

484
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:36,600
(CREATURE ROARING)

485
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:38,400
(DEEP-ANDO SCREAMING)

486
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:40,680
(DEEP-ANDO BREATHING HEAVILY)

487
00:20:49,840 --> 00:20:51,040
(BEEPING)

488
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:57,200
(ROARING)

489
00:20:58,480 --> 00:20:59,480
(SIGHS)

490
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:03,080
Uh, he was the first of them to die.

491
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:06,640
We heard the scream but um...

492
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:09,600
well we... (CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

493
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,600
We had our own problems.

494
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:15,200
(METALLIC CLANKING)

495
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:18,480
RASSMUSSEN: What's happening?

496
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:19,600
NAGATA: Engines?

497
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,840
CHOPRA: No, it's the gravity shields!

498
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:22,960
They're failing!

499
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:28,200
Nagata, that thing, the schematic.
Give it to me!

500
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:29,720
Who the hell do you think you are?

501
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:32,080
-Me? I'm in charge.
-You have no authority.

502
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:34,000
No. But I'm in charge.

503
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:35,440
I can bypass the main systems

504
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:37,160
and reboot the grav-shields.

505
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:39,280
CLARA: Listen to him for God's sake!

506
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:41,080
He knows what he's talking about!

507
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:43,080
(GRUNTING)

508
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:46,160
CLARA: Doctor!

509
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,720
Doctor, if the grav-shields
are decaying...

510
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,560
RASSMUSSEN: Don't say it.
Please don't say it!

511
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:53,360
CLARA: We're being pulled
towards Neptune.

512
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:55,680
RASSMUSSEN: Oh, gods,
oh, gods, oh, gods!

513
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,200
DOCTOR: Hang on!

514
00:21:59,080 --> 00:22:01,880
CLARA: (GRUNTS)
This day couldn't get any worse!

515
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:03,160
-(GLASS SHATTERING)
-(ROARING)

516
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:13,240
I can do this! I can fix this!

517
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:16,400
(RASSMUSSEN SHUDDERING)

518
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:19,560
RASSMUSSEN: Oh, please!

519
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:21,560
-(RASSMUSSEN SCREAMING)
-(ROARING)

520
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,360
CLARA: No! No!

521
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:33,680
DOCTOR: The G-Force is increasing

522
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:35,520
the closer we get to the planet.
Hold on!

523
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:38,840
(ROARING)

524
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:44,360
(BEEPING)

525
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:47,880
DOCTOR: We're back online!

526
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,520
Grav shields fixed!

527
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:50,600
We're rising!

528
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:52,560
Go! Let's get out of here.

529
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:54,360
Go, go! Out of here, come on!

530
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:56,560
NAGATA: Chopra, 474, come on!

531
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:59,040
DOCTOR: Keep going.
Move it, move it, move it!

532
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,600
Nagata!

533
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:03,200
No, I can't leave them!

534
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:06,720
NAGATA: Chopra,

535
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:09,520
474, may the gods... Where are you?

536
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:17,040
(CHOPRA BREATHING HEAVILY)

537
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:27,160
CLARA: Oh, God, of all the places.

538
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,400
A cold store.

539
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:30,600
-Nagata, are you okay?
-No, I'm not.

540
00:23:32,520 --> 00:23:33,920
-What about the others?
-I don't know.

541
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,720
-We have to go after them!
-Don't be ridiculous.

542
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:37,280
CLARA: Doctor!

543
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:40,240
They're under my command.
I owe it to them.

544
00:23:40,320 --> 00:23:41,560
To die?

545
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:43,240
They wouldn't thank you for that.

546
00:23:43,320 --> 00:23:45,440
Nor you, Clara. "To die, to die.

547
00:23:45,520 --> 00:23:47,520
"Glamis hath murdered sleep,

548
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:49,600
"therefore Cawdor shall sleep no more.

549
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,400
"Macbeth shall sleep no more."

550
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:54,600
NAGATA: What?

551
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,000
Shakespeare. (CHUCKLES)

552
00:23:58,240 --> 00:23:59,800
He really knew his stuff.

553
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,120
They all did.

554
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:04,800
The ancients. The poets.

555
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:08,200
All those sad songs,
all those lullabies.

556
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:14,600
Sleep is essential
to every sentient being in the universe.

557
00:24:14,680 --> 00:24:17,480
But to humans, greedy, filthy,

558
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:19,840
stupid humans,

559
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:24,120
it's an inconvenience,
to be bartered away.

560
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:26,000
Well, now, we know the truth.

561
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:30,320
Sleep isn't just a function,

562
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,560
it's blessed.

563
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:37,920
Every night we dive deep
into that inky pool.

564
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,960
Deep into the arms of Morpheus.

565
00:24:41,040 --> 00:24:44,440
Every morning we wake up
and wipe the sleep from our eyes.

566
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:46,680
And that keeps us safe.

567
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:49,000
Safe from the monsters inside.

568
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:51,240
Well, the bloody monsters
are outside now.

569
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:53,160
What do we do?

570
00:24:53,320 --> 00:24:54,440
(DISTANT THUDDING)

571
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:55,680
(GUN POWERING UP)

572
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:15,520
NAGATA: Dead meat.

573
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:22,880
(CHOPRA PANTING)

574
00:25:24,240 --> 00:25:27,480
Dear gods, what are we going to do?

575
00:25:27,560 --> 00:25:29,080
Get ship. Go home.

576
00:25:30,840 --> 00:25:32,360
We can't let those things off here.

577
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:34,000
If they were to get out, to spread,

578
00:25:34,080 --> 00:25:35,440
it's like an infection.

579
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:38,640
You don't understand, do you?

580
00:25:39,320 --> 00:25:40,920
Sleep men bad.

581
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:42,720
Kill sleep men.

582
00:25:42,800 --> 00:25:45,120
Yeah. That about sums it up.

583
00:25:46,760 --> 00:25:48,080
Chief Nagata, this is Chopra.

584
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:50,360
May the gods look favourably upon you.

585
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:52,640
(RADIO BEEPS)

586
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,960
Chief Nagata, this is Chopra. May the...

587
00:25:57,800 --> 00:25:59,840
We'll head for the rescue ship.

588
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:01,800
If we don't hear from them soon,

589
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:03,840
I'm going to have to
assume they're dead.

590
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:05,320
Then what Chopra do?

591
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:08,120
I have no choice.

592
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:11,560
I'll have to destroy this whole station.

593
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:17,280
(WHIRRING)

594
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:20,480
NAGATA: What're you doing?

595
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:22,080
DOCTOR: I've hacked
into your helmet cams.

596
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:24,080
-NAGATA: What?
-Reviewing the footage.

597
00:26:24,160 --> 00:26:25,400
There's something not right here.

598
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:27,520
NAGATA: We don't have helmet cams.

599
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:29,720
Why did it kill Rassmussen like that?

600
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:31,760
That's what they do, isn't it?

601
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:32,880
Kill people.

602
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:35,280
But that's a direct attack.

603
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:37,320
It's not how they operate.

604
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:40,000
Dust grows, consumes the host.

605
00:26:40,080 --> 00:26:41,640
They evolve. You said so yourself.

606
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:43,520
(SIGHS) Maybe.

607
00:26:44,080 --> 00:26:45,760
There's something going on here.

608
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:47,360
Something we're not getting.

609
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:50,120
(BEEPING)

610
00:26:50,280 --> 00:26:51,840
POD: Please stand clear of the pod.

611
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:54,040
Dangerous materials in transit.

612
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:56,360
What now?

613
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:58,080
We can't stay in here.
We're gonna freeze to death.

614
00:26:58,160 --> 00:27:01,240
We can't go back out there
because the Sandmen will get us.

615
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,400
(SIGHS)

616
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,000
Sandmen?

617
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:07,600
Yeah, it's a good name.

618
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:10,120
It fits. Like in the song.
# Bom, bom, bom... #

619
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:12,680
No. No, no, no, no.
You don't get to name things.

620
00:27:12,760 --> 00:27:15,040
I'm the Doctor. I do the naming.

621
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:17,440
CLARA: All right, sorry.

622
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:20,760
It's like the Silurians all over again.

623
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:23,600
CLARA: Okay. Well, what would
you prefer then, the Dustmen?

624
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:25,840
Sandmen.

625
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:29,280
What did you just say?

626
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:31,120
-NAGATA: When?
-1.83 minutes ago.

627
00:27:33,240 --> 00:27:35,560
I said we don't have helmet cams.

628
00:27:39,840 --> 00:27:40,920
(LOUD THUDDING)

629
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:42,560
(SANDMEN ROARING)

630
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:49,120
(THUDDING)

631
00:27:50,360 --> 00:27:51,360
(SOFTLY) Doctor?

632
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,040
(ROARING)

633
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:54,640
That door isn't going
to last much longer.

634
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:55,720
NAGATA: (SOFTLY) So what do we do?

635
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:58,120
(THUDDING CONTINUES)

636
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:00,440
We let them in.

637
00:28:00,520 --> 00:28:02,080
CLARA: What?

638
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:03,240
We let them in.

639
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:07,800
Mmm. It's clever, that.

640
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:09,520
Clever strategy.

641
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:11,160
If they'd stayed in there,
they'd have frozen to death,

642
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:13,720
so the Doctor had
to let the creatures in.

643
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:15,160
That was his theory.

644
00:28:16,680 --> 00:28:18,000
Oh, I'm not dead.

645
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:21,160
You've probably guessed that by now.

646
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:24,160
(HEARTBEAT POUNDING)

647
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:27,320
(SANDMAN MOANING)

648
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:36,320
(SANDMAN CONTINUES MOANING)

649
00:28:42,080 --> 00:28:43,080
(DISTANT RUMBLING)

650
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:45,160
474: What happen?

651
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:47,080
Must be damage from
when we fell out of orbit.

652
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:49,440
(BOTH COUGHING)

653
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,120
We have to go back.

654
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:55,280
(SANDMEN ROARING)

655
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:58,320
CHOPRA: I don't know what to do.

656
00:28:59,960 --> 00:29:01,360
I can't save us.

657
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:05,200
-474 can.
-What?

658
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:11,640
(SANDMAN HEAVING)

659
00:29:16,040 --> 00:29:17,880
(NAGATA BREATHING SHAKILY)

660
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:23,800
(MOUTHING)

661
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:28,120
RASSMUSSEN: The Doctor worked it out.

662
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:31,040
The creatures can't see.

663
00:29:34,960 --> 00:29:36,600
(SANDMAN HEAVING)

664
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:41,640
Shh!

665
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:55,400
DOCTOR: Run! Engine Room!

666
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:02,680
What happened?

667
00:30:04,160 --> 00:30:05,600
(STRAINING) 474 help.

668
00:30:06,760 --> 00:30:08,280
(474 WHEEZING)

669
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:10,440
CHOPRA: What?

670
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:14,120
474 die soon.

671
00:30:14,640 --> 00:30:16,240
No, no, no, don't say that.

672
00:30:16,320 --> 00:30:18,440
You got us through.
You can survive this.

673
00:30:18,520 --> 00:30:20,400
(SANDMEN ROARING)

674
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:22,920
474: Chopra go.

675
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:26,480
Get ship.

676
00:30:26,560 --> 00:30:28,640
(WHEEZING) Chopra be safe.

677
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:31,160
Chopra pretty.

678
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:33,880
(SANDMEN ROARING)

679
00:30:44,840 --> 00:30:46,200
(ROARING)

680
00:30:50,760 --> 00:30:52,000
(YELLING)

681
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:58,360
You said you felt like
you were being watched, Clara.

682
00:30:58,440 --> 00:30:59,600
CLARA: Paranoia, you said.

683
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:01,440
Not this time.

684
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:08,480
There is a feed. Wireless.

685
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:11,400
These images are being
stored by someone. Collated.

686
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:13,920
Nagata, look at this footage.

687
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:16,760
What's wrong with it?
What's wrong with it?

688
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:17,880
Don't know.

689
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:20,240
DOCTOR: Look, there's one
very obvious thing about it.

690
00:31:20,320 --> 00:31:21,520
Do you see it yet?

691
00:31:23,040 --> 00:31:24,040
No?

692
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:26,680
Okay, I'll tell you what's wrong.

693
00:31:27,760 --> 00:31:29,840
There's footage here of everyone.

694
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:31,640
But what's missing in all of it?

695
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:34,440
What can't you see anywhere?

696
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:38,240
Not in the footage, not on this ship.

697
00:31:39,240 --> 00:31:40,240
Look.

698
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:41,840
Really look.

699
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:45,960
There are no cameras here.

700
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:49,280
No CCTV. No helmet cams.

701
00:31:49,360 --> 00:31:52,520
So how and why does
this footage even exist?

702
00:31:53,440 --> 00:31:56,120
The dust has been watching us.

703
00:31:56,960 --> 00:32:00,640
Each little organic speck,

704
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:04,760
just a tiny spy,
drifting through the air.

705
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:07,280
The monsters have
been with us all along.

706
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:09,160
That's why the Sandmen are blind.

707
00:32:09,240 --> 00:32:11,440
Their visual receptors
are being hijacked!

708
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:12,920
But by whom and why?

709
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:16,400
And then, there's this.

710
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:21,000
That's you, Clara.
That's you looking at me.

711
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:23,680
Me?

712
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:26,920
You went into the pod.

713
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:31,280
The Morpheus process has begun.

714
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:32,880
(SIGHS)

715
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:33,960
Pod.

716
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:37,160
There's nothing here
from Chopra's point of view

717
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:38,960
because he refuses to use Morpheus.

718
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:41,200
But everybody else is here,
including you.

719
00:32:42,320 --> 00:32:44,440
You don't have a camera, Clara.

720
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:48,120
But will have by now, sleep in your eye.

721
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:52,600
Okay, well, we'll fix this.

722
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:53,920
You will fix this.

723
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:55,120
Yes.

724
00:32:55,560 --> 00:32:58,160
I'm sure it'll be fine,
I'm sure you'll be fine.

725
00:32:58,240 --> 00:32:59,240
Sure?

726
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:01,360
We will sort this, Clara.

727
00:33:01,440 --> 00:33:04,240
We'll sort you, we'll sort Nagata.

728
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:05,440
And everyone back on Triton.

729
00:33:05,520 --> 00:33:09,000
Then we will destroy Morpheus forever.

730
00:33:10,800 --> 00:33:11,840
Okay, then.

731
00:33:13,280 --> 00:33:14,600
Let's get on with it.

732
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:20,120
The power's been almost
entirely out since we arrived,

733
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:22,120
but we've still got emergency lighting.

734
00:33:24,520 --> 00:33:26,120
But the engines are still on.

735
00:33:26,800 --> 00:33:30,480
Well, there was that incident
with the grav-shields, but...

736
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:34,920
-Ah!
-CLARA: What? What? What? What? What?

737
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:37,840
The grav-shields didn't fail.

738
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:39,480
They were deliberately powered down.

739
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:41,760
NAGATA: By the Sandmen?

740
00:33:42,360 --> 00:33:44,560
Well, that's not their style, is it?

741
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,520
It's like...

742
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:55,520
It's like something's been kept here.

743
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:59,040
Near the engines where it's hot.

744
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:00,640
Like something's been...

745
00:34:01,560 --> 00:34:02,880
Kept alive.

746
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:07,600
POD: Warning!
Dangerous materials in transit.

747
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:09,840
Human contact not advised.

748
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:13,120
Warning! Dangerous materials in transit.

749
00:34:13,200 --> 00:34:14,800
Human contact not advised.

750
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:18,240
Well, you said someone's watching.

751
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:19,840
-Collating images.
-DOCTOR: Yeah.

752
00:34:19,920 --> 00:34:23,320
Well, if it's not the Sandmen,
then who is it?

753
00:34:24,560 --> 00:34:26,520
I have an idea who.

754
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:29,800
A very nasty idea.

755
00:34:34,600 --> 00:34:35,600
(BEEP)

756
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:37,680
CHOPRA: In the absence
of any further communication

757
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:39,120
with Chief Nagata and the others,

758
00:34:40,240 --> 00:34:43,760
I must regrettably assume
them to be deceased.

759
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:45,480
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

760
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:48,920
Under the circumstances,
I'm now returning to the ship

761
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:52,920
and will begin preparations
to destroy Le Verrier station.

762
00:34:56,120 --> 00:34:57,440
(SANDMAN GROWLING)

763
00:34:59,080 --> 00:35:00,640
(GUN POWERING UP)

764
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:06,680
(DISTANT THUDDING)

765
00:35:07,640 --> 00:35:09,520
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

766
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:10,840
Who's there?

767
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:12,000
-(DOORS HISSING)
-Chief?

768
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:23,360
(CHOPRA PANTING)

769
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:32,920
-(SANDMAN ROARING)
-(CHOPRA SCREAMS)

770
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:39,080
NAGATA: Rescue ship?

771
00:35:39,160 --> 00:35:40,680
Why are we going to the rescue ship?

772
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:42,240
DOCTOR: Because that's where he'll be.

773
00:35:45,720 --> 00:35:48,040
RASSMUSSEN: Gagan Rassmussen.
I'm Gagan Rassmussen.

774
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:50,600
This is Le Verrier lab
in orbit around Neptune

775
00:35:54,320 --> 00:35:56,200
I've put things together
into some kind of order...

776
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:59,120
You had that prepared
well in advance, didn't you?

777
00:35:59,200 --> 00:36:02,360
Your statement. Your alibi.

778
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:04,800
There would inevitably be questions

779
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:06,920
when you got to Triton.

780
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,480
So you needed to get
your story straight.

781
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:11,920
RASSMUSSEN: This is what happened.

782
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:17,880
You can't fight them, Doctor.

783
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:20,840
There's no point.

784
00:36:20,920 --> 00:36:22,080
They're the future.

785
00:36:23,080 --> 00:36:24,720
A new life form.

786
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:26,600
A better life form.

787
00:36:26,680 --> 00:36:28,760
It's very clear to me now. They've...

788
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:29,840
They've made me understand.

789
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:39,440
And we're to be their food,
and that's only correct.

790
00:36:39,520 --> 00:36:42,320
I just needed to find a way to get them
off this station and back to Triton

791
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:44,280
and then they'll spread.

792
00:36:44,360 --> 00:36:45,680
Spread everywhere.

793
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:47,040
And that's what you want?

794
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:48,960
You're helping them wipe out humanity.

795
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:51,480
Things have been made very clear to me!

796
00:36:51,560 --> 00:36:53,200
NAGATA: But we saw you die.

797
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:55,040
The Sandman swallowed...

798
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:57,360
I think the Professor has
been playing a long game.

799
00:36:57,440 --> 00:36:58,440
Am I right?

800
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:00,680
They speak to me.

801
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:01,880
In my mind.

802
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:04,520
Trust me, I think.

803
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:08,760
But they're like children. Babies.

804
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,160
So new.

805
00:37:12,080 --> 00:37:13,160
Evolving.

806
00:37:14,080 --> 00:37:15,720
Hungry.

807
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:17,360
Always so hungry.

808
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:19,480
I made them understand.

809
00:37:19,560 --> 00:37:21,360
We had to find a way out.

810
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:25,440
And then there'd be new food sources.
Unlimited.

811
00:37:25,520 --> 00:37:27,680
So they spared me.

812
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:28,880
And we waited.

813
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:32,400
You and your cargo?

814
00:37:35,040 --> 00:37:38,480
RASSMUSSEN: I got it in here
while you were all distracted.

815
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:40,360
(BEEPING)

816
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:50,440
CLARA: What's in there?

817
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:53,640
Dust?

818
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:59,520
It's like smuggling a jam jar
full of germs through customs.

819
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:02,880
No. No, more than that.

820
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:06,560
What do you mean?

821
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:10,600
I've been working on Morpheus
for a very long time, Doctor.

822
00:38:10,680 --> 00:38:12,240
I had to start somewhere.

823
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:15,080
Morpheus' first client.

824
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:17,440
Patient Zero.

825
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:21,080
The ultimate Wide-Awake.

826
00:38:22,720 --> 00:38:24,400
Inside there,

827
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:27,440
is @ man who hasn't slept in five years.

828
00:38:28,160 --> 00:38:29,400
Or what's left of him.

829
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:31,520
He's the well-spring.

830
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:35,800
Once we get to Triton,
he will spread his spores.

831
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:37,120
CLARA: But you said
it was an encoded signal.

832
00:38:37,200 --> 00:38:39,880
Something electronic
in the Morpheus process

833
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:41,480
that changed the chemical
reaction in the brain.

834
00:38:41,560 --> 00:38:43,560
Well, that's how it started, yes.

835
00:38:43,640 --> 00:38:45,360
But it's changing all the time.

836
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:47,400
Evolving new ways to infect.

837
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:48,800
To flourish.

838
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:53,600
Whole moons, whole planets,
whole civilizations.

839
00:38:53,680 --> 00:38:55,080
They'll spread everywhere.

840
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:57,040
You know I can't allow that.

841
00:38:57,120 --> 00:38:59,440
You can't stop them.

842
00:38:59,520 --> 00:39:00,600
None of us can.

843
00:39:00,680 --> 00:39:02,560
(GUN POWERING UP)

844
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:04,160
I wouldn't bet on that, pet.

845
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:08,120
(DEVICE BEEPS)

846
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:09,680
(KING SANDMAN GROWLING)

847
00:39:14,880 --> 00:39:16,000
CLARA: Doctor!

848
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:17,600
(KING SANDMAN ROARING)

849
00:39:17,680 --> 00:39:18,760
CLARA: Doctor!

850
00:39:22,920 --> 00:39:25,720
(SOFTLY) What he wants is to
get that thing off this ship.

851
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:28,000
-We have to stop him.
-Any ideas?

852
00:39:29,320 --> 00:39:30,800
The doors are not a problem.

853
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:31,920
CLARA: But...

854
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:35,960
(BEEPS)

855
00:39:37,320 --> 00:39:38,760
DOCTOR: We need a distraction.

856
00:39:44,680 --> 00:39:46,720
When I say run, run.

857
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:48,520
(KING SANDMAN HEAVING)

858
00:39:50,560 --> 00:39:52,000
Hey! Sandy!

859
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:54,440
# Bom, bom, bom, bom, bom, borm, born

860
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:56,200
-2 Borm, borm bormn, born, boron, borr...
-Run!

861
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,760
2~ Bom, borm bormn, born, born, boron, bormrm Z

862
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:00,320
DOCTOR: Doors!

863
00:40:01,320 --> 00:40:03,080
(MR SANDMAN CONTINUES PLAYING)

864
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:06,800
Rassmussen! Turn off the engines!
Shut the ship down!

865
00:40:06,880 --> 00:40:08,680
I can't do that I'm afraid, Doctor.

866
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:10,280
We can't fight the inevitable.

867
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:11,800
Humanity's day is done.

868
00:40:11,960 --> 00:40:13,240
NAGATA: Yeah? Well, humanity might have

869
00:40:13,320 --> 00:40:14,600
something to say about that, pet.

870
00:40:14,680 --> 00:40:16,720
-CLARA: No!
-(GROANS)

871
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:20,560
Is that your answer for everything?

872
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:21,720
Did you have a better one?

873
00:40:21,880 --> 00:40:23,400
DOCTOR: He's not the only one dead.

874
00:40:23,480 --> 00:40:26,200
According to this data, we're the only
ones left alive on this station.

875
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,200
(KING SANDMAN GROWLING)

876
00:40:29,520 --> 00:40:30,560
CLARA: Doctor.

877
00:40:32,120 --> 00:40:33,680
Come on, man! We've got to go!

878
00:40:33,800 --> 00:40:34,800
(BANGING ON DOOR)

879
00:40:35,040 --> 00:40:36,880
-This doesn't make any sense.
-CLARA: What?

880
00:40:36,960 --> 00:40:38,800
A man who hasn't slept for five years.

881
00:40:38,880 --> 00:40:39,880
Well, you heard what he said.

882
00:40:39,960 --> 00:40:41,040
That's the first Morpheus patient.

883
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:42,680
But the dust consumes the host.

884
00:40:42,760 --> 00:40:44,920
And then they make Sandmen,
they conglomerate.

885
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:48,960
Well, we escaped from that cold storage
room because they were blind.

886
00:40:49,400 --> 00:40:50,920
And why power down
the grav-shields when he did?

887
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,920
It's like... This is all for effect.

888
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:54,320
Look, can we maybe
have this conversation

889
00:40:54,400 --> 00:40:55,880
when we get off this thing?

890
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:57,520
Like a story...

891
00:40:58,440 --> 00:41:00,080
-NAGATA: Come on!
-(LOUD THUDDING)

892
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:01,560
(KING SANDMAN GROWLING)

893
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:05,200
(BANGING ON DOOR)

894
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:11,480
NAGATA: How do we get off this crate?

895
00:41:11,560 --> 00:41:12,960
DOCTOR: Alternative transport.

896
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:14,840
(GROWLING)

897
00:41:18,920 --> 00:41:20,200
We have to get to Triton.

898
00:41:20,280 --> 00:41:22,680
Destroy all the Morpheus machines.
End this.

899
00:41:22,760 --> 00:41:23,960
This is how we get home?

900
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:27,240
I've never been so pleased to see...

901
00:41:27,560 --> 00:41:28,640
(SANDMEN ROARING)

902
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:38,600
Nagata.

903
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:42,760
CLARA: Doctor, quickly.

904
00:41:43,640 --> 00:41:44,760
(DOCTOR MUTTERING INCOHERENTLY)

905
00:41:48,680 --> 00:41:49,680
What did you just do?

906
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,440
Self-destructed the grav-shields.

907
00:41:51,520 --> 00:41:52,560
NAGATA: What?

908
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:54,080
(ALL GRUNTING)

909
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:02,520
DOCTOR: It's working!

910
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:06,120
Neptune's gravity is pulling
them apart, bit by bit!

911
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:09,840
It doesn't make sense.
None of this makes any sense!

912
00:42:23,800 --> 00:42:24,880
Hello, again!

913
00:42:24,960 --> 00:42:27,360
The thing is, you see,
this message, this testament,

914
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:28,760
it wasn't just my alibi.

915
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:29,840
It was my plan.

916
00:42:31,160 --> 00:42:33,320
There are no spores, no infection.

917
00:42:33,400 --> 00:42:35,520
The Morpheus process remains the same.

918
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:36,600
An electronic signal

919
00:42:36,680 --> 00:42:38,720
that affects the sleep
centres of the brain.

920
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:39,840
It changes them.

921
00:42:39,920 --> 00:42:40,920
An electronic signal

922
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:43,280
that's contained in this recording.

923
00:42:44,400 --> 00:42:45,560
There it is.

924
00:42:45,640 --> 00:42:46,720
It tickles, doesn't it?

925
00:42:46,800 --> 00:42:48,720
I've just got time to fit this bit in

926
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:50,440
and then I can finish the story.

927
00:42:50,520 --> 00:42:52,320
And then I'm going to
transmit this footage

928
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:54,640
to the whole solar system.

929
00:42:54,720 --> 00:42:56,120
I do hope you've enjoyed the show.

930
00:42:56,200 --> 00:42:58,000
I did try to make it exciting.

931
00:42:58,080 --> 00:42:59,280
All those scary bits.

932
00:42:59,360 --> 00:43:00,760
All those death-defying scrapes.

933
00:43:00,840 --> 00:43:01,840
Monsters.

934
00:43:01,920 --> 00:43:04,080
And a proper climax with
a really big one at the end!

935
00:43:04,160 --> 00:43:05,720
Compulsive viewing.

936
00:43:05,800 --> 00:43:08,400
I did tell you not to watch.

937
00:43:09,840 --> 00:43:10,960
(GROANS)

938
00:43:12,840 --> 00:43:15,560
(IN DEEP VOICE) There's nothing left
of Rassmussen any more.

939
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:18,640
Only us.

940
00:43:19,880 --> 00:43:21,520
Only us.

941
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:26,240
You will show this film
to your family, won't you?

942
00:43:26,320 --> 00:43:28,080
And your friends.

943
00:43:28,160 --> 00:43:30,360
And everyone, really.

944
00:43:30,440 --> 00:43:33,560
And then we can all be together.

945
00:43:33,640 --> 00:43:37,000
Dust to dust.

946
00:43:37,080 --> 00:43:38,400
Excuse me.

947
00:43:39,560 --> 00:43:41,240
You've got something...

948
00:43:42,280 --> 00:43:43,640
There.

949
00:43:45,120 --> 00:43:47,960
Just in the corner of your eye.

950
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:51,000
(LAUGHING EERILY)

951
00:44:01,520 --> 00:44:03,680
Rigsy! Hey. What's wrong?

952
00:44:03,760 --> 00:44:06,120
So, I have this, uh...
It kind of looks like a tattoo.

953
00:44:06,240 --> 00:44:08,560
There's no nice way
to say you're about to die.

954
00:44:08,640 --> 00:44:09,680
What?

955
00:44:09,760 --> 00:44:11,800
I don't know who did this to you.

956
00:44:11,920 --> 00:44:13,760
But I do almost certainly know...

957
00:44:14,280 --> 00:44:15,280
How to find them.

958
00:44:15,720 --> 00:44:18,440
So, this your life then?
Bouncing around time, saving people?

959
00:44:18,640 --> 00:44:20,280
DOCTOR: There have always been rumours,

960
00:44:20,360 --> 00:44:22,320
mutterings about hidden streets.

961
00:44:22,400 --> 00:44:25,880
Secret pockets of alien life
right here on Earth.

962
00:44:26,640 --> 00:44:29,000
ASHILDR: Peace on this street
depends on one thing,

963
00:44:29,080 --> 00:44:30,720
to break it is to face the raven.

964
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:36,840
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

